INSTALL:
=======
We support only UNIX based systems (but the tagger is expected to work with Windows). There is nothing to do to install.

To tag the sample file given in this software, run this command

     make tag

The sample files provided with the tool are kannada.sample.txt and kannada_10m.txt (in data directory). Please change input file entry in Makefile entries accordingly. For more tagging options, use "./bin/tnt -h"

CONTACT
=======
Please drop us a line if you intend to use the tagger. We would be very happy to hear from you.

For additional corpora and tools for other languages, please email your queries to
siva@sivareddy.in or s.sharoff@leeds.ac.uk


TAGSET DETAILS:
==============
Fine Grained Tags 311 discarding low frequent tags.
Main POS Tag        25     CC, JJ, NN, VM, . . .
Coarse POS Tag      9      adj, n, num, unk . . .
Gender              6      any, f, m, n, punc, null
Number              4      any, pl, sg, null
Person              5      1, 2, 3, any, null
Case                3      d, o, null
